                    "description": "The DSM Biotechnology Center (DBC) is the center for biotechnological Research and Development (R&D) within DSM. The DBC steers the biotechnology competence within DSM and is responsible for the realization of biotechnological innovations and the development of new products and cost effective production processes for DSM business units such as DSM Food Specialties, DSM Anti-Infectives, DSM Nutritional Products, along with Emerging Business Areas for DSM such as White Biotechnology. He is responsible for all DSP activities.\n\nAs a principal scientist he develops a vision which is endorsed by senior management, stating how the scientific discipline and the technological patent portfolio are to be kept at a competitive level in order to be able to deliver suitable production processes in correspondence with the business needs. Furthermore, he is responsible for the quality of the work being executed within the department in order to adequately realize the business project goals. He stimulates the exchange of knowledge between professionals and work together with the center manager on technical equipment, technical education programs and resource planning. Additionally, he actively participates in and leads complex (business) projects as experienced scientist, advisor, projectleader or program manager.\n\n- Responsible -together with the center manager- for the (science and line) management of the DSP department (\u00b1 70 persons) in the DSM Biotechnology Center\n- DSM global champion separation technology\n- DSM program manager Corporate Research Program on downstream processing\n- DSM program manager Institute for Sustainable Process Technology (former Dutch Separation Technology Institute and Action Plan Process Intensification)\n- Member of several Industrial Advisory Boards for projects within the Separations branch of the Netherlands Organization for Scientific Research (NWO/Separations) and the B(E)-Basic (Bio-BAsed (Ecologic